## TinyFish Integration

### Client

- **File**: `src/server/lib/tinyfish/client.ts`
- Only place allowed to call `fetch` for TinyFish:

  ```ts
  const BASE_URL = "https://agent.tinyfish.ai/v1/automation";

  export async function runSSE(
    body: TinyFishRequest,
  ): Promise<TinyFishSSEResult> {
    const response = await fetch(`${BASE_URL}/run-sse`, {
      method: "POST",
      headers: buildHeaders(),
      body: JSON.stringify(body),
    });

    if (!response.ok) {
      // Read body text/JSON, surface error in TinyFishSSEResult.error
      return {
        success: false,
        resultJson: null,
        status: "FAILED",
        error: message,
        rawEvents: [],
      };
    }

    return parseSSEStream(response);
  }
  ```

- Headers must include `X-API-Key` from `env.TINYFISH_API_KEY`.
- `parseSSEStream` (in `sse-parser.ts`) builds `TinyFishSSEResult` from streamed SSE events.

### Goals

- All goals in `src/server/lib/tinyfish/goals/*.goal.ts`.
- Jobs goal (`jobs.goal.ts`) returns strict JSON schema:

  ```ts
  {
    "jobs": [{
      "title": string,
      "department": string | null,
      "location": string | null,
      "isRemote": boolean,
      "postedAt": string | null,
      "seniorityLevel": "junior" | "mid" | "senior" | "lead" | "executive" | null,
      "isNewProductSignal": boolean,
      "productSignalReason": string | null
    }],
    "totalCount": number
  }
  ```

- Mapping from `SourceChannel` → goal is done only in `scan.service.ts` (via `resolveGoal`).

